# 4.Given two integers, write a Python program that:Prints the result of a & b, a | b, and a ^ b.Shifts the bits of a two positions to the left (a << 2).Shifts the bits of b one position to the right (b >> 1).
# Take input from user
a = int(input("Enter first integer (a): "))
b = int(input("Enter second integer (b): "))
# Bitwise operations
and_result = a & b
or_result = a | b
xor_result = a ^ b
# Bit shifting
left_shift = a << 2
right_shift = b >> 1
# Display results
print("\nResults:")
print("a & b =", and_result)   
print("a | b =", or_result)
print("a ^ b =", xor_result)
print("a << 2 =", left_shift)
print("b >> 1 =", right_shift)
